# felix-ui — Project overview

## What this is

**felix-ui** is an enterprise design system: an internal React component library for consistent UI across products.

## Stack

- **React** 19, **TypeScript** 5.7 (strict)
- **Tailwind CSS** v4
- **Rollup** — dual **ESM + CJS** build
- **Storybook** 8.5
- **Radix UI** (`@radix-ui/react-slot` for `Button.asChild`, etc.) where needed

## Zero-CSS architecture

Components use Tailwind class names as strings in TSX. Consumers compile CSS (Tailwind); the library does not ship a separate CSS bundle that components depend on at author time beyond tokens/theme conventions.

## Folder structure

Components live under `packages/ui/src/components/`:

- `Atoms/` — current public components (**Button**, **Text**)
- `Molecules/` / `Organisms/` — reserved for future work; may be empty

## Classification

- **Atom** — Smallest visual unit; little or no complex state. Current examples: **Button**, **Text**.
- **Molecule** / **Organism** — For future compound or complex UI when the design system expands.

## Design tokens

Single source of truth: `packages/ui/src/tokens/tokens.ts`.

## Primary consumer

**payments-ui** — Next.js 16, Node 24.

